cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DC

This paper is about improving the performance of training and deploying convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses hardware architectures and optimizations, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on improving the efficiency of deep learning could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
